  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Riding Dog",
      "sources": [
        {
          "errata": {
            "alt": "1.1",
            "aonid": 221,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "1.1",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "link": {
            "alt": "Monster Core pg. 102",
            "aonid": 221,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Monster Core pg. 102",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core",
          "page": 102,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "Riding dogs types include larger dogs, such as mastiffs, wolfhounds, and huskies, and are bred often by halflings and gnomes to serve as mounts. Riding dogs are as loyal and devoted to their masters as guard dogs and ferocious in battle, regardless of whether they bear a rider or not. As with guard dogs, these large hounds can be wild or feral in nature, and in such cases might rival wolf packs in the danger they pose to inhabitants of rural areas.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
